Configure Dashboard Data Visibility in Lightning Experience

To change the running user and control which data is visible to viewers:

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS:
- To create, edit, and delete dashboards created by you in a public folder: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards AND Edit My Dashboards
- To edit and delete dashboards that you didnâ€™t create in a public folder: Manage Dashboards in Public Folders
- To create, edit, and delete dynamic dashboards: Manage Dynamic Dashboards
- To specify a running user: View My Team's Dashboards OR View All Data

Edit a dashboard, click , and select the running user. You can choose Me (your access to data), Another person (the specified user's access), or The dashboard viewer (dynamic dashboard based on their privileges).

To enable viewers with permissions to choose who they view the dashboard as, select Let dashboard viewers choose whom they view the dashboard as.

Click Save twice. When a user opens your dashboard, they see data as the person you specified.
title: Configuring Dashboard Data Visibility in Salesforce
